  Name: B-2 Spirit
  Information: The Northrop Grumman B-2 Spirit is an American heavy strategic bomber
    featuring low-observable stealth technology designed to penetrate dense anti-aircraft
    defenses. Capable of delivering both conventional and nuclear weapons, it has
    a 172-foot wingspan, a 6,000+ nautical mile unrefueled range, and a crew of two.
    Only 21 were built, with an approximate unit cost of over $2 billion.
  Manufacturer: Northrop Grumman
  Date: 1988
